Dialogue: 10,0:01:36.76,0:01:39.63,Top,,0,0,0,,Hey, let's go around the farm on our way back.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:39.63,0:01:40.88,Top,,0,0,0,,Yeah, sounds good!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:53.60,0:01:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, sheep! {referring to them colelctively here}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:56.08,0:01:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{yahoo}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:05.11,0:02:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:06.43,0:02:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:08.03,0:02:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh... I fell on my butt.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:10.73,0:02:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,That sounds like gunshots.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:12.37,0:02:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe someone's hunting?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:14.97,0:02:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe they're shooting wild dogs? {actually norainu is stray dogs but at 2:52 they say "it was shot by mistake" and idk how to make this work otherwise since it's a stray dog alright, just not the dangerous kind of stray ig}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:17.67,0:02:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Wild dogs?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:18.77,0:02:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The sheep should be lambing soon.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:21.81,0:02:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a crucial time, so the farmers shoot any dogs that come near, lest they frighten the sheep.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:29.92,0:02:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's just hurry home.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:31.25,0:02:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:50.74,0:02:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that a wild dog?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:52.41,0:02:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The farmer shot it by mistake!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:58.31,0:03:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,See? It must still have a bullet in its leg.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:00.88,0:03:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Poor thing!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:02.12,0:03:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, if we leave it here, it'll die, won't it?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:04.50,0:03:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got to take it \Nto the vet as soon as we can!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:07.99,0:03:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no vet in this area. \NI'll heal it myself!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:11.14,0:03:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? How?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:13.66,0:03:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take it with me to the school. {and let it heal there}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:15.56,0:03:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? To the school?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:17.26,0:03:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't we try calling the police? \NThe owner might be looking for it.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:20.60,0:03:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Later.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:21.70,0:03:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now it needs its wounds seen to at once.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:27.38,0:03:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But you're not allowed \Nto bring pets to school!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:31.75,0:03:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So are you saying we leave it here to die?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:35.58,0:03:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely not!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:37.74,0:03:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s all right now. \NWe’ll have you mended in no time.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:49.83,0:03:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you tired?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:50.83,0:03:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll manage. More importantly, \Nwhere should we take it next?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:53.52,0:03:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The bicycle shed is frequented by a lot of people. {meaning you can't keep it there}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:56.57,0:03:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,How about the gym storage shed?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:58.41,0:04:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That also has a lot of people \Ncoming in and out.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:01.34,0:04:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, how about the dorm closet?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:04.15,0:04:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Good idea! We'll be able \Nto check on it often enough in there, too.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:07.65,0:04:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I just hope none of the mistresses find it there...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:41.01,0:04:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So far so good.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:43.38,0:04:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,How's the puppy?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:44.92,0:04:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:47.84,0:04:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What's fine?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:50.81,0:04:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:54.06,0:04:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,C'mon, don't scare us like that!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:56.16,0:04:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! What's that, a dog?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:00.17,0:05:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's injured.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:01.47,0:05:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll look after it until it recovers.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:03.50,0:05:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet, are you going to town now?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:06.07,0:05:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I was going to...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:07.21,0:05:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But I wanna help too!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:08.30,0:05:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you go to town and ask the police \Nif there's anyone looking for it. {the puppy}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:12.28,0:05:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Want me to go to the police?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:13.71,0:05:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Please!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:14.98,0:05:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We need your help!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:16.02,0:05:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, please!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:17.43,0:05:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,A-All right, all right.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:19.85,0:05:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I know Kathleen can quite lose herself \Nwhen it comes to animals.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:26.63,0:05:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel, there's an old wooden box \Nin the storage shed. Could you bring it?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:30.80,0:05:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:46.78,0:05:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We should be safe after making it this far.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:54.72,0:05:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,This way...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:55.72,0:05:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{?}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:00.09,0:06:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,No way! {ikan?}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:04.30,0:06:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Quick!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:16.61,0:06:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Oh, Pat?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:18.66,0:06:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:21.75,0:06:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you make that sound? \NI thought I heard a dog's bark.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:25.20,0:06:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? N-No, that was...
Dialogue: 10,0:06:29.39,0:06:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not hiding any cats here, are you? {because she's afraid of them}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:31.68,0:06:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,N-No, none, madam.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:40.63,0:06:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing, Pat?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:44.12,0:06:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,R-Right, I was tying my shoe...
Dialogue: 10,0:06:49.08,0:06:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:50.44,0:06:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What was what?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:52.10,0:06:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard some whimper. {nanka kuun kuun tte - something did kuunkuun = whimper/whining}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:56.85,0:06:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Sniff-sniff... {not sure if english even has an onoma for this action pat is doing now, but probably not whimpering, right?}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:58.10,0:06:59.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:59.49,0:07:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I wonder if I caught a cold... {hanakaze = head cold}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:01.46,0:07:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodness!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:03.86,0:07:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like you don't have a fever.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:06.06,0:07:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s an epidemic raging, so do take care.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:08.31,0:07:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:10.06,0:07:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Geez... {mou}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:20.87,0:07:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Ready? Hold it down real tight now.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:37.86,0:07:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Bear with it. \NJust a little more.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:48.99,0:07:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally! I did it! {I don't know what's more laughable here - the fact some farmer shot the dog with normal bullets and not pellets, or the fact that the puppy survived it}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:52.44,0:07:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank god!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:53.67,0:07:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't let go yet! \NI have to apply the medicine too.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:56.46,0:07:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:59.91,0:08:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You're great at this, Kathleen!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:01.95,0:08:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to be a veterinarian when I grow up.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:05.02,0:08:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Good to know.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:07.59,0:08:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You're lucky that wound wasn't deep, \Nso you should recover in no time.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:11.02,0:08:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You did well bearing with it!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:16.30,0:08:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,There, you can sleep undisturbed here.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:20.10,0:08:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Shouldn't we feed it at least something?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:22.47,0:08:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Better to do that after a nap.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:24.30,0:08:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,My, it's starting to doze off already!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:27.21,0:08:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s been through so much today—\Nfrightened and shot at, hurt and in pain.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:31.44,0:08:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this a terrier?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:32.81,0:08:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:33.90,0:08:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But terriers are ten a penny \Namong themselves too.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:36.65,0:08:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The Medium Airedale Terrier is a police dog.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:39.45,0:08:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Small Scottish Terriers \Nand Yorkshire Terriers are lapdogs. {愛玩 = caring for (esp. a pet or a small object); cherishing; being fond of; prizing; treasuring}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:44.59,0:08:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Bull Terriers, crossed with Bulldogs, \Nmake excellent guard dogs.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:49.10,0:08:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, you know so much about it!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:51.56,0:08:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you already started studying to be a vet?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:54.87,0:08:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Sort of.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:56.84,0:09:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I still haven’t the slightest idea \Nwhat I want to do in the future.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:00.01,0:09:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We should be more like you. {?? lit: gotta learn from them}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:01.61,0:09:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So what's this puppy? {meaning "what breed"}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:02.71,0:09:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yorkshire Terrier.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:04.18,0:09:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,As it matures, its fur grows \Nincreasingly long and fluffy.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:07.88,0:09:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, it's asleep already!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:09.55,0:09:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right! \NIt's adorable!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:20.03,0:09:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no one looking for a dog?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:22.88,0:09:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what they said.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:24.20,0:09:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What a relief!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:25.30,0:09:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:26.00,0:09:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I just...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:27.40,0:09:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,They asked the name and address of the person \Nwho found it, so I gave them Kathleen's.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:31.87,0:09:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But if the police call the school, \Nthe mistresses will find out at once!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:36.81,0:09:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But I couldn’t very well leave \Nwithout telling them that.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:40.01,0:09:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, by the way, I bought this!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:42.62,0:09:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Dog food! Clever!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:51.12,0:09:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That gusto is amazing! {lit: amazing drive/impetus}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:53.08,0:09:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems it was really hungry, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:55.46,0:10:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,If it had developed such a strong appetite already, \Nthat must mean its wound is healing up nicely.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:00.80,0:10:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Already?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:01.70,0:10:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, dogs heal quickly.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:04.60,0:10:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we must take it out for a walk \Nbefore going to sleep.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:07.11,0:10:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? You mean outside?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:08.48,0:10:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s got to relieve itself somewhere. {lit: we gotta let it pee}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:10.34,0:10:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I wonder if there's a shovel somewhere here.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:12.91,0:10:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to make sure to clean up after it...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:14.38,0:10:16.88,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, I'll go look for it.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:30.00,0:10:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't have to worry \Nabout being spotted out here.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:34.07,0:10:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Look how delighted it is!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:35.79,0:10:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, Isabel, this shovel \Nis way too big for what we need!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:39.37,0:10:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re not here to plough fields, you know.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:41.54,0:10:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I know, all right. \NI'll try to find a smaller one later.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:45.18,0:10:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Shh! Someone's coming.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:53.36,0:10:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's me!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:00.86,0:11:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Girls!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:04.80,0:11:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the one!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:06.13,0:11:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So cute!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:09.24,0:11:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You told them? {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:10.54,0:11:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it best to let everyone know \Nabout this sort of thing?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:14.27,0:11:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right! He belongs \Nto all of the first form now.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:17.74,0:11:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I told them you're only going to keep it \Nuntil its leg heals. {??}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:20.78,0:11:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Th-Thanks... {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:22.25,0:11:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But Hillary...
Dialogue: 10,0:11:24.38,0:11:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I protest it!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:25.92,0:11:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The school rules make it perfectly clear that you can’t bring pets to school, let alone keep them here!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:31.06,0:11:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you going to report it to the mistresses, then?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:33.72,0:11:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,If we let it go now, its leg will worsen \Nand the puppy will die! {lit: if it moves here and there}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:38.00,0:11:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that what you want?!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:48.88,0:11:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I get it, all right.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:53.88,0:11:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But in return, if something happens to it, \Nyou will all take responsibility.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:16.67,0:12:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,A small announcement before we start the class.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:19.77,0:12:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,A student was caught secretly keeping a bird \Nat St. Christopher's the other day, {??? I thought st. crist's was a public school where they went home for the night so how tf would that happen?}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:23.91,0:12:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and was consequently expelled.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:27.20,0:12:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no doubts in our own students, \Nbut would still ask you to be careful.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:33.25,0:12:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us start the class now.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:46.03,0:12:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think Miss Roberts knows already?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:48.33,0:12:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:49.14,0:12:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a coincidence. {that she told us about it this morning}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:50.02,0:12:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But being expelled would really sting.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:52.27,0:12:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you, scared? {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:53.24,0:12:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 10,0:12:54.10,0:12:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But what are we gonna do if it's discovered?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:56.34,0:12:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you make absolutely sure \Nit never gets discovered. Got it?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:59.81,0:13:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:12.89,0:13:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What is that sound?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:20.77,0:13:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a dog! A dog is whimpering. \NYou hear it too, don't you?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:28.21,0:13:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Mam'zelle! You must be mistaken. {soramimi = mishearing - basically she says "what you're hearing is not what you think you're hearing" but idk, english doesn't have a good word for that; in book: “You must be mistaken, Mam’zelle,” said Doris, gravely.}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:30.81,0:13:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Mistaken?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:32.03,0:13:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way there's a dog in the school!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:34.81,0:13:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Th-That's right! \NThere aren't any dogs here!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:36.85,0:13:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't hear a thing!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:37.93,0:13:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! I don't hear anything!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:40.05,0:13:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Quiet now! {\i1}Silence!{\i0} {pronounced "see-lahns" in french}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:43.32,0:13:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I know there are no dogs at St. Clare's.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:46.53,0:13:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Only the kitchen cats to catch the mice.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:49.06,0:13:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Still...
Dialogue: 10,0:13:50.00,0:13:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Écoute!{\i0} {listen! / hear?}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:50.86,0:13:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? {??? maybe "nothing!"}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:52.40,0:13:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, it must be something wrong \Nwith my ears, then.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:55.74,0:13:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I have dogs barking \Nand whining in my head.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:58.22,0:13:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}C’est sûrement! {that must be it!}{\i0}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:01.87,0:14:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Take down a dictée! {/write down}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:11.60,0:14:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That was close.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:13.42,0:14:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The puppy must be feeling better today, \Nthat's why it started barking out loud.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:17.29,0:14:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What are we gonna do?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:18.39,0:14:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What if we soundproof the room \Nby hanging blankets on the walls?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:22.33,0:14:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That's our Hillary!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:52.26,0:14:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,One, two, three, four...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:54.10,0:14:55.96,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Exercising in a place like this?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:55.96,0:14:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! To work up an appetite before dinner.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:58.76,0:15:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,To work up an appetite?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:00.60,0:15:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you stop saying nonsense\N and step away for a moment?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:03.30,0:15:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to leave this in the room.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:06.36,0:15:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Please let me put it away for you!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:08.80,0:15:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:09.51,0:15:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,More importantly, Matron, \NI think our roof is leaking! Please take a look!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:16.65,0:15:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,All clear. We got rid of her. {/drove her away}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:27.89,0:15:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems its leg has already fully recovered.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:30.08,0:15:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,True. That was fast!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:32.80,0:15:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if we'll be able to keep it forever.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:35.20,0:15:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just thinking that same thing too!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:37.80,0:15:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Me too.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:38.84,0:15:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Me too!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:40.14,0:15:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, no...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:40.91,0:15:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you're responsible forever \Nfor what you have tamed, but... {??? unsure what she means so sneaking in a quote: https://medium.com/@janaspartadutra/you-become-responsible-forever-for-what-you-have-tamed-the-true-meaning-behind-this-quote-77e2c1569e32}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:43.98,0:15:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Our soundproofing worked so well too!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:46.44,0:15:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Only for now, okay? {probably means "you can only keep it for a little longer"}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:48.28,0:15:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Mam'zelle will have another class tomorrow.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:51.32,0:15:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And she has such good hearing...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:58.36,0:16:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I can't ever let it go! {/part with it}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:07.93,0:16:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The mistresses will hear you!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:14.82,0:16:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Quel jour sommes-nous? {jme says it means "What day is it?" but i decided to just keep the french text and not bother with a tl; maybe add it as a note if we really feel like it}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:16.66,0:16:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,On divise l'année en 12 mois. {We divide the year into 12 months.}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:19.51,0:16:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Ce sont: janvier...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:22.32,0:16:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:23.90,0:16:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,mars, avril, mai, juin... {They are: january, oh, march, april, may, june...}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:48.68,0:16:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Get back here!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:56.05,0:16:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! I said stop!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:11.13,0:17:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:15.44,0:17:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Headmistress! Catch that dog!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:17.90,0:17:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Dog?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:22.89,0:17:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,G-Goodness me... {????}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:27.13,0:17:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Get back!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:28.58,0:17:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on here?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:48.00,0:17:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Quick! Somebody!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:49.10,0:17:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,This is getting out of hand! {??????}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:52.94,0:17:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What's all that racket outside?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:13.76,0:18:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Q-Quiet, please!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:19.43,0:18:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:27.11,0:18:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh-la-la!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:28.71,0:18:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So when I heard a dog whimper the other day, \Nit wasn’t my ears after all? What a relief!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:36.17,0:18:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen, Isabel, Pat, \NI believe you all owe us an explanation.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:42.09,0:18:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be waiting in my room.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:52.70,0:18:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course we knew \Nyou can't keep a dog at school.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:55.80,0:19:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But I simply couldn't bring myself to leave that dog to its fate, injured and in pain!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:01.34,0:19:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,S-So we decided to only take care of it \Nuntil it's injury heals.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:05.41,0:19:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We have also notified the police \Nin hopes of locating the owner.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:10.62,0:19:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Get back, all of you!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:12.55,0:19:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,How abominable!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:18.49,0:19:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter, everyone?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:21.29,0:19:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Those three weren’t looking after that dog \Nby themselves. We all helped!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:25.66,0:19:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,G-Girls...
Dialogue: 10,0:19:28.27,0:19:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right! \NSo you'll have to expel all of us!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:43.42,0:19:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hallo, police? {from book}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:45.48,0:19:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Miss Theobald, \Nthe headmistress of St. Clare's school for girls. {from book, she's old but she's still miss there so that's canon ig}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:49.79,0:19:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's about one of my students finding a dog...
Dialogue: 10,0:19:52.96,0:19:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:54.19,0:19:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:57.40,0:19:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:04.24,0:20:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I see no reason to blame you \Nfor taking care of a puppy in distress. {/poor puppy}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:09.28,0:20:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,No, on the contrary, as the headmistress \Nof this school, I am proud
Dialogue: 10,0:20:13.58,0:20:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that you did not abandon that suffering puppy \Nand instead saved its life.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:19.45,0:20:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how small a life is, \Nit is irreplaceable.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:23.59,0:20:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,To cherish and value that life \Nis the most important thing.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:29.03,0:20:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, it doesn't seem likely \Nthat this puppy's owner will be found.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:33.07,0:20:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The police also said \Nwe can keep it for all they care. {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:37.07,0:20:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,As such, you are allowed to keep it here \Nuntil you go on vacation.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:40.66,0:20:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Headmistress!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:42.61,0:20:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Hooray!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:45.21,0:20:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, now... {????}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:49.88,0:20:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Headmistress, but what are we \Ngoing to do after vacation?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:53.35,0:20:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see now...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:56.05,0:21:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,How about taking it to Kathleen’s aunt \Nor the O’Sullivans’ place, if either of them agrees?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:05.10,0:21:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It pains me, but you deserve it. {lit: it's a shame, but I relinquish my right}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:06.83,0:21:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. After all, you're the lifesaver \Nwho healed the puppy's injury, Kathleen.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:11.60,0:21:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:14.61,0:21:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, what is the name of this puppy?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:18.58,0:21:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... We haven't given it one yet.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:20.75,0:21:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,How about "Binks"?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:22.38,0:21:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:23.32,0:21:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know why, but I've been wanting \Nto name him that for a while. {??? dunno what she says/means; in the book:  I don’t know why—but he looks like a Binks to me.}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:27.42,0:21:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That's such a classy name!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:29.09,0:21:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, let me ask him. {in the book it's a boy btw}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:31.02,0:21:33.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Binks, do you like it?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:33.93,0:21:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that sounds like a "yes!" {???? dunno, lit: the thing about good state - maybe "he's recovered completely"}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:38.68,0:21:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, Binks!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:40.75,0:21:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:41.77,0:21:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:48.31,0:21:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve never seen our first form students so united.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:52.81,0:21:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the students \Nwho taught us something this time.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:55.55,0:21:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Excusez-moi? {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:56.52,0:22:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,A true education is impossible if you constantly \Nrestrict students with school rules.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:03.22,0:22:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 10,0:22:13.00,0:22:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{???}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:35.88,0:23:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat, just imagine for a moment.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:38.45,0:23:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,If we show the best possible result on the next exam, how happy do you think Dad and Mum would be?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:42.71,0:23:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Mum would throw a huge party as if it were both a birthday and Christmas at once!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:46.64,0:23:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad never praises us,
Dialogue: 10,0:23:48.38,0:23:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,but I'm sure he'll brag about us this time. {????}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:50.06,0:23:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,"Well, it turns out my naughty twins \Ncan be quite capable too!"
Dialogue: 10,0:23:54.47,0:23:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly like that, Pat! {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:56.70,0:23:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time on Twins at St. Clare's:
Dialogue: 10,0:23:58.40,0:24:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,"Isabelle is Cheating?!" {イザベルがカンニング!?}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:59.32,0:24:04.31,Note,,0,0,0,,Episode 11 \NIsabelle is Cheating?! {イザベルがカンニング!?}
Dialogue: 10,0:24:00.07,0:24:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't miss it!
